{
  "texts": [
    "Given multiple tissue sections from the same patient at up to 20× magnification, HistoGPT uses a vision foundation model to extract meaningful features from the images and combines them with a large language model (LLM) via cross-attention mechanisms to generate a pathology report.",
    "Each generated report describes the tissue composition, cellular subtypes, and potential diagnosis.",
    "In addition, users can interact with the model through various prompts to extract additional information such as tumor subtypes, tumor thickness, and tumor margins (Fig. 1b).",
    "The output text (Fig. 1c) is fully interpretable with saliency maps that highlight the corresponding image regions for each word or phrase in the generated text.",
    "Fig. 1 | HistoGPT, a foundation vision language model for dermatopathology."
  ]
}